==English==
===Etymology===
From [[quasi-]] + [[hemi-]] + [[demi-]] + [[semi-]] + [[quaver]].

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''quasihemidemisemiquaver'''
#{{music}} (Principally UK) A [[note]] having a time value half as long as a [[hemidemisemiquaver]] or [[64th note]].  

===Synonyms===
*[[128th note]] [[hundred twenty-eighth note]] (US) 
*[[semihemidemisemiquaver]]